load ../chat-fork.maude

--- The corruption pattern throughout: a QUIET instance whose own line's
--- head folds more turns than its thread remembers -- files from turns
--- the conversation has never heard of.

--- Hazard demonstrated: a shared-branch fork lets the fork's turn move
--- the source's line. The source (quiet, thread z) then sits on a head
--- that folds a turn it never took.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkShared(i1, i2) quiet(i1) inst(i1, z) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, z) go
  =>* quiet(I:Iid) inst(I:Iid, N:Cnt) bound(I:Iid, B:Bid) br(B:Bid, H:Cnt) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that lt(N:Cnt, H:Cnt) .

--- Hazard demonstrated: a mid-turn fork births an incoherent instance --
--- the forked branch already carries the in-flight turn's writes, the
--- seeded thread does not.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkMid(i1, i2) quiet(i1) inst(i1, z) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, z) go
  =>* quiet(I:Iid) inst(I:Iid, N:Cnt) bound(I:Iid, B:Bid) br(B:Bid, H:Cnt) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that lt(N:Cnt, H:Cnt) .

--- Hazard demonstrated: seeding the thread at an older coordinate while
--- forking the branch at head births the same incoherence.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkStale(i1, i2, z) quiet(i1) inst(i1, s(z)) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, s(z))
  =>* quiet(I:Iid) inst(I:Iid, N:Cnt) bound(I:Iid, B:Bid) br(B:Bid, H:Cnt) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that lt(N:Cnt, H:Cnt) .

--- Bite: under the sound fork (quiescence + fresh branch at head + seed
--- at the latest turn) the corruption pattern is unreachable, however
--- the fork and the turns interleave.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkReq(i1, i2) quiet(i1) inst(i1, z) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, z) go go
  =>* quiet(I:Iid) inst(I:Iid, N:Cnt) bound(I:Iid, B:Bid) br(B:Bid, H:Cnt) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that lt(N:Cnt, H:Cnt) .

--- Bite: the sound fork never shares a line -- two instances bound to
--- one branch are unreachable (divergent histories of "the same" run
--- cannot exist).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkReq(i1, i2) quiet(i1) inst(i1, z) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, z) go go
  =>* bound(I:Iid, B:Bid) bound(I2:Iid, B:Bid) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that I:Iid =/= I2:Iid .

--- Coverage: the fork lands and advances its OWN line; the source's
--- branch never moves.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkReq(i1, i2) quiet(i1) inst(i1, z) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, z) go
  =>* inst(i2, s(z)) bound(i2, nb(i2)) br(nb(i2), s(z)) br(b1, z) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: the fork preserves the source -- it keeps taking turns on
--- its own line while the fork's line stays put.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CHAT-FORK :
  forkReq(i1, i2) quiet(i1) inst(i1, z) bound(i1, b1) br(b1, z) go
  =>* inst(i1, s(z)) br(b1, s(z)) inst(i2, z) br(nb(i2), z) RESIDUAL:Cfg .
